title: Smells like you are on a Caribbean vacation!
text: What is better than sitting on the beach sipping a cool, refreshing mixed drink? What could make it better - incorporating a nice, hot bath while sipping that drink! So, what is the closest thing you can do if you can‚Äôt go on said vacation? Well, take a bath in something that smells fruity and fun! The ‚ÄúYou Clean‚Äù bath salts bring both of these elements (a drink and a bath) together. This Fizzy Foaming Bath Salt smells faintly of ‚ÄúSex on the Beach.‚Äù It smells absolutely delicious and isn‚Äôt overwhelming at all! This product comes in a 17oz resealable bag, filled with a dusty/fine/colorful powder in bold/bright/colorful colors:  hot pink, yellow and orange. The salts are a combination of Epsom and Mediterranean Sea salt, which is very soothing and relaxing. It is sulfate, paragon, gluten and phthalate free. Overall, this is decent product that will make a nice gift for yourself or someone else. 4 stars.

title: awesome
text: Oh, my goodness! I cannot believe that we have actually found some earrings that my daughter can wear!  She has had her ears pierced a couple of times but had to let them heal up due to allergic reactions to the metal, even gold. Wearing these she has had ZERO issues. They are so light she forgot they were on her ears. There was no pressure from the silicone hook. They just hook on the lobe or the cartilage. They aren't super tight so don't go swimming or other crazy activities in these, they will come off. But she wore these all evening with absolutely no issues. No itching, no pus pockets, no hives, nothing. She just about started giggling to the point of wheezing from happiness that she has one pair of earrings to wear now. And they are lady bugs! How amazing is that! She loves ladybugs.

title: Pretty color, good sized stone.
text:
Love this brand, and have several. Highly highly recommend for self or gifts!!

This bracelet is exactly what I would hope it to be. Included both sides of the stone for reference. Mine came is more pink than the ones in the listing photos but differences are to be expected between stones. I didn‚Äôt understand the listing about the clasp and the magnetic part. I thought maybe it would be a magnetic clasp. It is not so there‚Äôs a photo showing that it is meant to slide over hand onto your wrist and tightened by pulling on both strings. The magnets are the decorative beads at the end of each. As you can see from the photo, the beads do attract together if messed with or if you shake your hands a lot but I don‚Äôt see that as a problem. This has a sturdy cord and the brass fixings help to keep your adjustment in place work very well. This is a great business to support!

title: A great looking handmade genuine obsidian Pendent !
text:
I got this because my son absolutely loved the amethyst one this company makes. And he likes this one equally as well. The amethyst one came off at foot ball practice and he lost it ! (why he was wearing it in football practice I'll never know) I plan on replacing that one for his birthday.

Now I worked in the jewelry business during my college years and fell in love with gemstones. Obsidian definitely falls into that something you don't see everyday. Which I love. Also the stone is rough cut but polished so it's undeniable that it's real. And the best part being handmade no two are the same which makes it super unique !

It looks fabulous ! Now for gender that's gonna be your personal call. My son being 5'7 looks better with the small one. His best friend ( who is getting the other one for his birthday gift) is 6'1 and bigger and he looks better with the larger one. My son is using the chain from the amethyst one for his obsidian and wearing the beautiful chain with solid links in it, solo. So you can see you can mix and match here with your personal like.

I have nothing but good things to say about this product and it definitely deserves all 5 stars and more ! Hope this was helpful .

title: Slightly disappointed in the snow camo
text: These earrings came packaged beautifully and with Care in a box with a card showing the store/creator of the item. I love black white gray anything accessory wise and love Graham my camouflage. So when I saw these I was extremely excited to see an earring the likelihood of potentially wear with some of my black and gray and white camouflage clothing. When I got the earrings I was a little surprised at how thick the wooden circle is that the earring base is made of. More than that, I was disappointed even more with the poor quality of the image that was used under the resin on the wood. The image was very pixelated and very washed out so anyone looking at them not knowing what I ordered would have a tough time nailing down why the pattern was intended to be. I know that all of them are going to be different because they are handmade, but not being able to discern the pattern that was used to make them because of the poor image quality extends beyond the idea that all of them are going to be slightly different.

title: Unique moon and star necklace features a freshwater pearl
text:
What makes this necklace unique is the delicate detailing in the design. A freshwater pearl is perched above a crescent moon under two small but bright cubic zirconias. A star attached directly to the neck chain is two inches above the moon and pearl. The chain is half a herringbone link on one side and a larger rectangular chain link on the other. Holding the necklace together is a small clasp.
The piece is made of 925 sterling silver plated with a gold finish. The chain is a little over 17 inches long. It would make a nice gift for someone looking for a necklace that stands out and can be worn casually.

title: They weren't kidding...
text:
A little goes a long way!

The first time I used it I did not heed the warning and wound up with greasy roots. Greasy roots that felt and smelled wonderful! But still...

The second time I was more careful and rather than apply to my scalp area while the hair was wet I used it after blow drying most of the way. My hair was still damp but mostly dry. I also concentrated on the tips rather than the roots and found that this worked much better. My hair goes past my collar bone and I have quite a lot of it. It's color treated so the ends are dry. I was able to use a dollop the size of a dime to cover my whole head. This tiny tub will last awhile! I don't think I'll use it daily though. It's a special treat.

I love the fact that it came from a small business as well. Support local!

title: Great for Sensitive Ears & Perfectly Sized!
text:
This product came adorably packaged. If you‚Äôre a sucker for adorable little boxes, you will love it!
The Thank You card had a generous discount code on it for a future order from their store.
When I opened the box everything came off with the lid. I‚Äôm removing the stuffing, I realized the earrings had stuck to the top of the box and peeled a bit of it off, which was stuck to the earrings themselves. I simply scratched the paper off with my nail. Probably could have done something else to remove, but, I wanted to see how durable the surface of the earring was! Everything was just fine. I still give these earrings 5 stars because a simple packaging fix, maybe some wax paper in the lid of the box or a tissue paper wrap and boom, problem solved.
I love the wooden accent that encases the color portion of this earring. That was a pleasant surprise.
If you have small ears, which I feel I have, these earrings are the perfect size. Once you put them in, you literally forget you have earrings in. They are weightless, and great for sensitive ears. Normally my ears will start itching within the hour. Not with these adorable little stud earrings! I also ordered the Black pair, which are arriving today!! Hoping the packaging issue was just a fluke, maybe caused by humidity and travel? The quality of the earrings themselves, excellent! I‚Äôm a fan!

title: Suds up and moisturizes very well but I'm not used to the smell
text:
I loved the simple packaging and beautiful handmade bars and think that these would make great gifts and could be individually wrapped for that purpose. I like how natural they are and they do make me feel very clean. However, this was my first time using a more natural soap like this, and it may take some getting used to. It actually out-performed my expectations with its cleansing and sudsing abilities. And it moisturizes as well or better than the high-end traditional bars of soap that I usually buy specifically to moisturize. It's heavy and might outlast other bars. That being said.. the smell though... I think it may be the lye. I am definitely not used to that. It's actually quite powerful. This bar's smell may be nothing compared to other makers that use the same process, but I'm not able to compare as this is my first time using. The strong smell is the only issue I have- but I would consider purchasing these again if other natural bars all have this same smell, because they work great!

I came back to edit this review- I'm not changing the stars from 4 because the smell was something to get used to, but I had to add that while my daughter and I were very sensitive to it, it's my husband's favorite. He LOVES the smell on me and says it's his favorite soap he's ever used. It does work very well and is lasting a long time! I'm going to have to order these again because he loves them so much and the smell has grown on me a little.

title: If it's the only one you've seen you'll love it
text: These are trendy. I purchased one off a different site, actually a video game I was playing was promoting it on one of their ads. I ordered it and I loved that one. And so did my best girl friend. She traded me a painting she did for my necklace. So I ordered this one to replace the one I used to love and wear all the time. This one is like a school grade of B- or C+ or even C- compared to the similar priced A+ one I used to have, as far as craftsmanship goes. The idea is the same but this one is lighter in weight with more clear resin. And the resin edges on this one are very square. The other one I had was smooth and rounded and didn't look like it came out of a resin mold. This one does. The other one was like a small miracle where you couldn't tell what was going on. You thought it might be one rock that was all those colours. But somehow this one you can tell it's smaller rocks inside clear poured resin. And it has those rougher pointy edges. This chakra style pendant is popular from many vendors right now and I am sorry to say I've experienced better craftsmanship. But you and your giftable friends may not have. So go for it, it's still pretty and cool.

title: Leaves my skin feeling clean and healthy!
text:
I REALLY like the YouClean - All Natural Creamy Coconut Soap! It reminds me of the soap my grandmother used to make! - clean, natural, no frills, but works beautifully!

The soap has no added fragrance, but yet it does have an old fashioned soapy odor, if that makes sense, which is not unpleasant. The bars are an off-white color.

The soap lathers beautifully, rinses well, and leaves my skin feeling clean and healthy! I have sensitive skin, and I'm happy to report that I've experienced no redness, no irritation from this soap.

The bars arrived undamaged, wrapped in tissue paper inside a white corrugated sleeve. The product is handmade in California.

Overall, I really like the YouClean - All Natural Creamy Coconut Soap! This is a product I would purchase again.

5 stars and recommended!

title: Price doesn‚Äôt equal value
text:
I was really excited to receive these earrings, but what I got didn‚Äôt quite measure up to what I expected.

The earrings themselves do look like the listing, but the gold is brighter and very cheap looking in person. The opalite looks nice, but it definitely is synthetic at a glance. If you‚Äôre looking for earrings that look well-made and authentic, these are not the right earrings for you.

They arrive in a box, but instead of actually being inserted into the box foam (like earrings from a retail store) they are inside inside of a fashion jewelry labeled plastic polybag. This in and of itself is by no means an issue, except for the fact that it made my earrings smell incredibly bad.

The earrings that I received smelled like chemicals when I took them out of the bag and the smell was strong enough that even after using a jewelry cleanser, I could still smell that chemical stench whenever I am in the same room, making it unpleasant to wear them.

Overall, the earrings do look nice but they look more like costume jewelry than anything legitimate. I would recommend them for some thing like a cosplay costume and not to coordinate as part of a standard outfit.

Pros:
- Looks like listing photo
- Parts can be worn together or separately

Cons:
- Smelly
- Bright gold coating looks cheap in person
- Opalite is obviously synthetic

title: Nicely Packaged and Pretty
text:
The HOMHOW triple protection bracelet arrives attractively packaged in a little linen covered box. The bracelet is held and displayed inside in such a way that it is laid out nicely on opening (it is not just floating around loose).

The bracelet itself is very pretty, with polished hematite, tiger's eye, and a blue stone I cannot identify. I am not sure which stone on here is supposed to be obsidian. I did not get this for healing or protective properties so a lack of a type of stone does not bother me. I got it because I like how it looks. To be fair, I DO like that it is heavy enough that I am aware of it on my wrist. If stuck in a conversation I am not enjoying this bracelet gives me something else to think about so maybe it relieves stress in that way.

I like how the size adjusts. It is easy for one person to put on and adjust. There are two ties on the underside --I call it the underside as it is where the adjustment is and it neatly stays put on the underside of my wrist -- which pull in opposite directions to make the bracelet smaller. As these ties get longer, the bracelet gets smaller. Cool! They do not loosen over the course of the day wearing it so the bracelet does stay at whatever size you adjust it to be.

I got this for myself, but this would also make a great gift.

title: Far From Expectations
text:
The Organ 7 Chakra necklace is... well, no other way to put it. It is disappointing. It arrived nicely packaged in its own little box with a pull tab. On opening, I was expecting something a bit more finished looking. This looks like a beginner's attempt at making resin "art" with rocks and a squiggle of copper.

The resin is chunky and a little cloudy, the edges were sanded, sure, but not sanded and cleared. Honestly, the rocks inside the resin may be rocks but they look more like little chunks of paper. If one was looking for a necklace for crystal healing purposes, this is not it. Even for an interesting necklace to wear without seeking healing, this still is not it. You could get away with giving this to a 6 year old and they would probably think it's cool as long as they still color outside the lines (their critical eye has not yet developed).

title: Fake quartz
text:
[[VIDEOID:55c113c35a14996b1d88e9e4c5a1b7f1]] The packaging smelled really bad of chemicals when I opened it. After obsessing over what the smell was..I discovered it was the paint they used on the pink one to make the gold look.
I do like the grey flint arrowhead but the ‚Äúrose quartz‚Äù is absolutely fake. I was able to make a deep cut in it with the point of the flint one. Besides the fact that it is soft enough to scratch, it‚Äôs also a really bright shade of pink that I‚Äôve never seen before. I think it might be resin‚Ä¶
The necklaces that it came with had such a strong scent to them that I had to leave them outside for a week and they still smelled. I‚Äôm not sure if it was the dye they used to make them black or if it was from the painted pink arrowhead but either way, I couldn‚Äôt keep them. The necklaces were basically two pieces of leather strap that they tied into a necklace shape..they way it was done was very loose and haphazard..I wouldn‚Äôt have trusted the knots to stay in place.
So..I definitely wouldn‚Äôt recommend this set unless you‚Äôre ok with a fake quartz. As I said, the flint one was nice but even that one had a strong scent to it from being packaged with everything else.

title: Charming and Versatile
text: If you can buy only one pair of dressy earrings for a teenage girl, I would recommend this pair.  They can be worn four ways:  The stud alone (a dressy daytime look), with the drop in front of the earlobe (for a charming evening look), with the drop behind the earlobe (for a sophisticated evening look), or with the drop on only one ear for avant-garde asymmetry.  In any of the three latter looks, the swinging pearl speaks of youthful energy as it swings back and forth with every little nod and shake of the head.  The pearls are of good quality for the price.  They come with an informational card on pearls to begin a teen's education in fine jewelry.  Overall, a very nice starter package for a young lady!

title: This little charm saved my dog

title: Wonderful lip balm. Don't like packaging
text:
I love the lip balm. It has a nice flavor (I got the vanilla strawberry) that is very moisturizing. It might go on a little thick initially, but it absorbs quickly and leaves my lips soft.

What I don't like is the packaging. I know it's supposed to be sustainable, which is great. But...

It is a very odd size and too wide around. Putting it in your pocket feels very weird because it's such a wide tube. Because it's so wide, it's also awkward to apply.

You move the lip balm up by pressing up through the bottom. The first one I tried, the whole inner portion of the packaging moved with the lip balm. I had to try to hold onto the packaging just to get the lip balm to move. The other balm that came in the box didn't do this, so I'm sure it was just that one that didn't work correctly.

I think this would be a great product if the same lip balm were to be packaged differently.

title: Great scent. Doesn't fizz much.
text: I loved the scent of these bath salts (peach bellini). The water turned a very nice color, which was also great for the experience. The first time I used it, I didn't use very much, and there wasn't a strong scent, so the second time, I used more. I feel like the packaging could use some kind of label with the scent, ingredients, and instructions, so people know what they have and how to use it. The only way I knew what this was was because of the Amazon inventory barcode label. Not great, especially if I were to give this as a gift and someone was allergic or sensitive to an ingredient.

title: Super cute!
text:
This is several sets of the same stickers and they couldn't be cuter. Literally just little tarot cards and the cheat sheets with quick blurbs about each card.
My friend and I were discussing how we could use these other than purely decoration, because I can totally see myself putting these on things just for the imagery. I think they would be great visual aids in a journal or planner to put in your weekly reading on a calendar. I have a monthly planner and was thinking I could also do a single draw and put the sticker on the month as a reminder of what I need to work on.
If you are learning, or teaching tarot reading, these would be GREAT for setting up a sample reading and seeing how it can be interpreted. Just pick a few and put them in the layout you are working on, and see how well you read without the cheat sheet.
I also think that if you do readings for others, you could use the stickers to do a visual of their reading that you could write the reading meaning on that they could take with them. If you are making a spell or mystery confetti mix, you could also cut these into induvial sheets and do a random pull and send a tarot sticker with!

I think there's multiple uses for these if you actually do readings. Even if you don't and you just like the imagery or just like the witchy vibe aesthetic, these are really cute and nice quality stickers.

title: Mood Bracelet
text:
Well, this is an interesting item. It's a bracelet with several thermochromic beads -- i.e. they change color, depending on the ambient temperature.

I think the manufacturer is suggesting that these change colors when your body temperature changes with your mood swings.

For the life of me, though, I can't correlate the colors of these beads with either mood swings or body temperature!

I can say that the thermochromic beads have changed from green to blue to brown to black during the course of the last day. Sometimes I've seen the beads showing both brown and green at the same time!

In short, I like these just for their novelty and changing colors, even if I can't gauge my mood or body temperature from the colors...

Otherwise, the bracelet string is quite long, so each bracelet should be able to fit wrists of many circumferences.

Cool!

title: Kid-friendly! Bath-resistant toddler now ASKS for banana bath!
text:
My boy is 3. I think it's the dirtiest phase kids go through, and mine is super resistant to take baths because he knows it means bedtime is close behind. When this came in, I could faintly smell the banana in the shipping box--smells very much like banana laffy-taffy, maybe a hint of coconutish-vanilla? Very yummy! It was a warm shipping experience, and the product was a bit clumpy once it cooled to room temp (I think this coconut oil-related, totally normal). I smushed it around in the bag to break up and mix it all evenly; the bag was sturdy enough to take shipping and smushing abuse without the seal breaking. (Forget the layers--shipping is going to mix these; mine was a pretty golden-yellow when it arrived.)

When it was bathtime, I asked him if he wanted to take a banana bath--it's his fave fruit, so he was hesitant but agreed once I let him smell the open bag. I used about a 1/4 of a cup for his bath, about 6 inches deep in a standard tub. The coconut oil clumps were a little slower to melt, only because his bath isn't adult-hot, but with a little mixing and hand-smashing (he loved that part!) it was fully mixed. Water was a light yellow and milky; very smooth on the skin, and smells amazing! He let me do all the hair routine stuff he usually fights me on, and then played in the bath another 15 min after all our official business was done. He splashed it all around in his face, and it didn't seem to bother or sting his eyes; we also wiped his eyes/face several times with the washcloth that was soaked in bathwater, no issues with it bothering him. He has sensitive skin, weird out-of-nowhere topical allergies/eczema-like flare-ups, but this product caused no such problems and after bath his skin was super-soft!

Rinsing the tub with hot water afterwards removed most of the residue and all of the dye color (very light pink-orange ring). I followed up with about 30 seconds with one of those spin-clean shower brushes, hot-rinsed and there was no staining.

I didn't notice any "fizzing" but we didn't use a lot and I wanted it for the scent and skin softeners and it totally delivers on that front. We got about 2 weeks of kid bathing out of this bag (we used this brand's Peach Bellini once, and mixed the two on another night). It's probably a little expensive for kids UNLESS you have one who's stubborn about bathtime. But, it would make a great "spa day" treat for your little one if you didn't want to use it day-to-day. You could also use this as a foot or hand soak; my hands are way softer two weeks into his banana baths, so it's working a little magic for mommy in the background! I also love that this supports a small business. 100% SOLD on this product, really hope it shows up in subscribe-and-save.

text:

BUT I literally cannot clasp this necklace. I have longer nails and the clasp is so incredibly tiny. The part on the spring ring is difficult to pull back and the loop it clasps to is on a tiny bead, which makes it even harder to hold steady. And the bead can easily be pulled off the chain bc there‚Äôs a flat bar instead of a bead at the end. I realize not everyone has long nails and I had a friend who clasped it for me very quickly, so I still would recommend this‚Ä¶.but beware if you have long nails and don‚Äôt have a buddy handy to help you out.

title: My new favorite necklace
text:
This has quickly become my go-to necklace. It's super cute and I love the dainty size. The stone is cut beautifully and I like that it's knotted in place on the cord. I'll admit that I don't know much about sacred geometry and that I just love amethyst in general. However, its meaning is something I could use in my life right now.

I really love the message of the company behind the necklace as well. I love supporting small businesses and it's so cool that the woman behind the piece signs the card. I love that some of the proceeds go to non-profits and that the necklace was packed in a fully biodegradable bag. This is the type of business I want to keep coming back to and give my support.

I only have a couple really minor complaints. The necklace is glued to the backing card with some overly-sticky adhesive. It was pretty stuck to the back of the amethyst and wasn't coming off easily. I didn't want to try anything too rough for fear of scratching the stone (I really have no idea how tough amethyst is). The cord also feels a tiny bit flimsy, though the packaging says it's tough and it hasn't shown any signs of breaking. I'm just paranoid about losing jewelry.

I would definitely recommend this necklace, whether you're into sacred geometry or just love its beauty. I always want to see more support for small artisan businesses that are doing good in the world.

title: Perfect for Non-Verbal Communication
text:
These are a really cool idea, and great if you live abroad from your family, are in a long distance relationship, have a penpal, or are separated from your loved ones frequently.

It was a little difficult for me to set up initially but I think it was on my end (Huawei phone had issues pairing with the device initially) though I ended up being able to pair it nearly instantly with my android tablet so once the initial set up is complete it will be synced in with your wifi and you can just login to the app from whatever device you want.

So now it works on every device, even my phone it previously was not pairing with.

Once paired they are super user friendly and simple to set up, you can use the preset colors as well as generate your own custom colors to set and you can set any color to be any meaning so it is customizable in just about every sense.

You can control it via the app or the built in touch/tap system on the top of the lamp itself. Both allowing you to change and send whatever colors (along with their designated meanings) to your friends, family, and loved ones.

The fact that they have sets for groups is also really fun for friend groups who may be going away to different schools to stay connected.

I like that it's a non invasive means of communication.
There's no tones or sounds, it's just a colored light , which I find soothing.

The perfect tool for non verbal communication, or even to develop your own silent way of communication.

Want to let your kids know it's time for dinner, for their friends to get headed out, or to turn down their tv/music without yelling around the house or charging in the room?

This is the perfect solution!
The app also digitally notified you of changes with your lamp so even if they are plugged in and tuned out it's still likely they will see some form of your communication.

Overall , I think the price is a little steep,
but I also understand making a device that is capable of doing everything it does all around the world and connected to wifi and Bluetooth is probably not an easy task,

so if it's something you think would be a fun way to communicate it's worth it because it's fun, unique and like a secret code.

title: Very pretty and unique necklace!
text:
This is a beautiful, complicated necklace. I love it! It can go with a patterned outfit and complement the colors and design or it can be the focal point of a monotone outfit offering an eye catching detail. It is very well made, each chain is secure. The clasp can be attached to a whole length of links adjusting the length to suit the neckline. The chain is a nice brass color, not a bright gold, which I find much more appealing. All the colors on this necklace are absolutely beautiful. I got a ton of compliments the first time I wore it.

The one problem I had is pictured. I have this problem with many necklaces, even when others don't, but any multistrand or necklaces with strings (or "worms" in the description) get tangled up on me. I had to take this off a few times during the course of the day to unwrap the chains from one another and from the base chain. Still worth it, and it still had an appealing enough look even when it was tangled, in my opinion. I really like unique jewelry, and this is an absolutely beautiful, affordable piece that looks decent quality and coordinates with so many things.

title: Smells amazing! Leaves skin soft, toddler friendly
text:
I love the scent! Smells just like the cocktail (banana-coconut-pineapple), and my toddler loves it too. It doesn‚Äôt seem to irritate his eyes when he splashes around in the tub, and doesn‚Äôt irritate his sensitive skin. We love this brand and have tried several scents. We don‚Äôt use much, about a 1/4 cup for a 6-inch bath, but it leaves an amazing soft scent behind on his skin, and softens my hands with every bath!

Shipping is not kind to these packets. The colors do not hold the separate colored layers and they mix in the bag, so anything with pink and green becomes tan-brown, as did this one. The bath water was a gray-brown milky color, almost like we‚Äôd poured a cup of cocoa or coffee in the bath, so not the most aesthetically pleasing, but the scent and smooth skin more than make up for it.

Overall, we‚Äôre hooked on these, and even though it‚Äôs a little expensive for toddler bathing, I don‚Äôt mind because it helps a small business and my little one doesn‚Äôt fight me at bath time anymore. Hoping to see these in subscribe and save selections some day!

title: Best Pearl Necklace I Have Seen In A While-LOVE IT
text:
I have never really wanted a pearl necklace because they look so perfect. I tend to like pearls which have some unique shape to them. This necklace is perfect.

HOW THIS COMES
This comes in a velvet bag and a gift box. It also has a cleaning cloth.

CLASP
This is an easy to use clasp which is large enough so I don't have to fuss with it.

PEARLS
These pearls are beautiful. Each one has a different shape to it, but they work together beautifully. The pearls have knots between them so if it breaks, you won't go chasing them all.

QUALITY
I have to say this is the only pearl necklace I honestly can not wait to wear. The unique quality of the pearls is wonderful. I really like it.

THE BOTTOM LINE
This pearl necklace for the price is beautiful for a gift. If you like perfectly round pearls, maybe you won't like it, but for me it is gorgeous.

MY RATING

title: All about the lustre
text:
Just like diamonds and their 4Cs, pearls have a set of criteria that can be adjusted to determine their worth: color, surface, lustre, shape, and size. I would rank this pearl necklace, high on color, surface, and luster, but low on shape. The size is just perfect for my desires.

I might point out that this necklace has 16 inches of pearl, but it is longer than 16 inches when the clasp is included, so it does not quite fit up close to the neck as one might wish for a pearl choker.

Overall, this is not my favorite pearl necklace, but considering how much Crane pearls usually cost, it's a decent value. It would be a good as a "can you take care of nice jewelry" test for a very young girl. It is pretty enough not to be ignored, but it is not as precious as other pearl necklaces.

title: Kid-friendly! Bath-resistant toddler now ASKS for bath time!
text:
Granted, this is a little expensive for kids. But, if you, like me, have a kid that resists bathtime, try some of these bath salts. For us, it really made things go much more smoothly, to the point that the kid now asks for his bath each night. The smell is amazing -- fruity and rich, just like a Mai Tai -- and it makes my hands and my toddler's skin SO SOFT. We don't use much, only about 1/4 cup for 6-8 inches of bathwater, but it's plenty to give off that "you want to be in here" scent and color that my toddler craves. It doesn't seem to burn his eyes, and even with eczema and sensitive skin, he has no issues with this product.

I will say that in shipping, this product sometimes gets beat up. So, the layers basically mix together, and if you have a green hue and a pink/red hue in the same bag, it basically shows up to your doorstep as a tan-brown. No big deal for functionality, but probably don't order this as a gift, or you might find yourself stressing a little when it arrives unlayered.

This is from a small business, and I think it's important to support these folks whenever we can. If I have to pay a little more, I'm willing to do it. I'd have paid twice this amount for the results I've gotten, so it is a good deal!

text: I've never met a pearl I didn't like ! This set is lovely, whether for yourself or a gift. If you're planning to gift it, you'll want to open it first and re-arrange it as each piece is wrapped separately to keep them from getting scratched. The color on the pearls was white, and they were well matched. I examined the pendant with a loupe and did see a 925 silver stamp. Silver and pearls can be a tough combination as it's hard to clean the silver without damaging the pearls, so I hope it's coated in something. text: [[VIDEOID:f19bff8ef23fee4eef0a31347a62930c]] This bracelet is gorgeous! The beads are larger than my other bracelet that‚Äôs similar to this one. The Yellow Tiger Eye stone beads are so beautiful! You can really see the definition of color with these 10mm beads! This bracelet is heavy which I like as I think authentic Tiger Eye, Obsidian & Hematite should be a little heavy especially for beads this size! It comes with extra beads and string just in case you need it to fit larger wrists you can add these beads onto the bracelet to create the desired length. I really love this bracelet and it‚Äôs $26.99 as of today but for authentic stones of this size plus the extra 4 beads and string (Yellow Tiger Eye, Hematite & 2 Obsidian beads) it‚Äôs a good buy! I only docked a star because I don‚Äôt know how to weave the extra beads onto the bracelet if it had been too small for my wrist but thankfully it wasn‚Äôt! These beads are woven tightly together which just adds to the beauty of the bracelet. Care instructions say this bracelet can be soaked in pure water, hand washed and then put it where the Sun & Moon can shine on it to recharge its magnetic and healing properties. I‚Äôm still learning about these stones and I may do that after I have worn it for a while but for now I‚Äôm just going to enjoy wearing it and all the compliments that I‚Äôm receiving! title: Let someone know you're thinking about them -- finicky WiFi set-up but afterward works great
text: As someone who lives across the country from most of my family, these little friendship lamps are great. It‚Äôs a way to stay connected and let someone know you‚Äôre thinking about them, no matter how near or far. I use these with my mom, and even though we‚Äôre on different time zones, it‚Äôs a simple way to keep in touch. I love them. As far as getting them connected to WiFi‚Ä¶ That, I do not love. It‚Äôs a bit of a hassle and if your internet goes out and you‚Äôre offline for longer than two seconds, you will more than likely have to go through the struggle of connecting them again. At least that has been my experience. For my mom, she‚Äôs had no WiFi issues since we set them up, so honestly, take my experience with a grain of salt, I suppose. So, either way, once you get them set up, these are a true joy. You can even select your particular color, and I know some people use them to send non-verbal reminders based on the particular color. For my mom and me, we just tap it every now and then when we walk by, but it means just as much to us as if we were sending special top-secret messages, lol ‚Äì so, this is a win for me.

text: These are really lovely earrings.  I liked them when I saw them online in the pictures, but the pictures just don't do them justice. title: Pretty hair tie
text: I was excited when I saw this colorful hair tie and ordered it. It came with a pretty cloth gift bag, for those who want to give it as a gift. I wish it came in a wider range of colors. It has just the right amount of flexibility to wind around my hair. I was excited to use it. The first three times I tried to use it on my long straight hair, it slid down my hair within 30 minutes, no matter how tight I tightened it. I gave up and secured my hair with a small hair tie first before using this spiral lock hair tie. Finally, my hair is secure and it does look pretty. I am giving this item a four star rating because there is no mention in the instructions of needing to secure your hair first before using this tie. However, when secure, it is pretty and I would buy it in other colors.

title: What metal are they?

title: This makes a great gift!
text:
My favorite gemstone is Tiger's Eye due to the fact it's known for inner strength and self-confidence. I have always wanted a bracelet which this gemstone on it but I never found one I liked until now. This bracelet is amazing and the gemstones on it are so pretty!

My favorite part about this bracelet is how well-made it is. It's very versatile and could fit many types of wrists due to it being easy to loosen or tighten. I also got the 10mm size beads on it and it's perfect for me! It has a good weight to it which I like; however, if you wanted it a little smaller and lighter I would recommend trying the 8mm size. The gemstone beads on this are incredible to look at and I love the Tiger's Eyes designs showing that it's authentic. You will also notice is ask Black Agate and Hematite are included as well which I also love. I also love how the bracelet is put together and it makes it feel extremely durable and no worries of it falling apart or breaking.

Overall, I love this bracelet and how well it's made. I love how it's authentic Tiger Eye as well as the other gemstones being authentic as well. I highly recommend this to either buy for yourself or this would make an amazing gift to friends and family.

title: These make me laugh hard enough to almost make me feel Christmassy.
text:
These are hilarious. Look at these grumpy slashers covered in Christmas lights AND holding jack-o-lanterns! Dual holiday coverage, which works for my decorating style. If only they were also holding a turkey ‚Äî or electric carving knife‚Ä¶ The product on hand is brilliant. I got the 6 pack, which is definitely the best value. They‚Äôre small, like 3 inches tall, but that‚Äôs good because otherwise they might be too scary. Both sides are printed, so if you hang this in your car, everyone will be able to see that you have a bizarre sense of humor while you also enjoy giggling at your serial killer freshening your car‚Äôs odor. I couldn‚Äôt wait to unwrap one, so I‚Äôve hung it on my desk lamp. It smells pretty good, typical ‚Äúcar air freshener‚Äù smell, but I can‚Äôt pin down which flavor. Ooh, another idea for the manufacturer, make pina colada scent (my favorite) and add the turkey/carving knife, so I won‚Äôt have to change the decorations until the new year.

I just got these, and I had to come in and review them given the misleading reviews I read when I ordered them, so I do not know how long they will last, scentwise. I suspect it will be about as long as any air freshener of this type, so a week or so. But I have 6 to swap out, so it should be good. When they‚Äôre done smelling, they will make great Christmas tree decorations.

For the record, these are flat, double sided, air fresheners, much like those ubiquitous pine trees. They are not figurines, nor would I expect that at this price. Each option is labeled clearly there are 1, 3, 4, and 6 piece sets. Obviously the larger sets are better values, but if you have your heart set on a Pennywise, you might have to shell out more. These are hilarious, and would also make great stocking stuffers or gifts if you can resist unwrapping them all to decorate your own space.

title: Beautiful and Beautiful Packaging, Too!
text: This pretty piece of jewelry caught my eye. I didn't know much about Moissanite, but it's super-sparkly! I like the design of the necklace, the stone itself, and all the little details. I was also super-impressed with the packaging: it comes in a nice heart-shaped walnut box in another leatherette box, and there's a little envelope with a polishing cloth and a serial-numbered warranty card, too. All of this makes it look and feel much more expensive than it actually is, but don't think this is some tacky piece of cheap jewelry because it is not. It's really lovely! Worn with the right dress, people will probably think it's a $10K diamond, and I certainly won't stop them from thinking that!

title: Truly sustainable w/ vegan formula; the clove is an interesting flavor/ scent
text:
J&L Naturals Sustainable Lip Balm is a truly sustainable product; from the stickers to the packaging, every piece is recyclable or biodegradable. The lip balms arrive in a cardboard box sealed with a low-adhesive sticker. Opening the package presents you with another sticker on the lid letting you know that your purchase planted a tree through #TEAMTREES; a QR code and web address provide you with a link to more info. The box is filled with Kraft paper crinkles to protect the lip balms in transit. The Lemongrass and Clove scent/ flavor was a pleasant surprise and a change from the usual flavors/ scents.
The tubes of lip balm are where sustainability genuinely shines; the cardboard tubes push up rather than twist, and the balm itself is wider for better coverage. This formula is created from six safe, simple vegan ingredients: Organic Coconut Oil, Extra Virgin Olive Oil, Shea Butter, Candelilla Wax, Lemongrass Essential Oil, and Clove Essential Oil. There are six scents available, and one of them is unscented if you have sensitivity.
The Bottom Line: At $27.49, each J&L Naturals sustainable tube is ~$5.50 each and holds more than twice as much as a standard plastic tube, which is excellent news for your bottom line. The vegan plant-based ingredients and plastic-free packaging are a boon for the planet. J&L Naturals Sustainable Lip Balm is a win-win product all around and would make a great stocking stuffer.

title: Stylish accessory for an outdated monetary transaction system
text:
I would really like to be able to do away with written checks altogether, but my landlord won't do Venmo or Zelle. He still wants that written check each month. So, for as long as I'm here, I'll have to keep a checkbook around.
If you're in the same boat, the least you can do is give your checkbook a stylish upgrade. This handmade leather checkbook cover does the job, and isn't something that would make me feel embarrassed or old to have sitting around on my desk. My bank wanted to charge me $25 for a cheap plastic cover to go with their checkbooks. For the same price, this is much better and better-looking.

text: Finally found true a minimalist wallet! After searching for so long and purchasing and returning countless wallets! title: Real amber beads
text:
I love the color of these beads and was excited to get them in. I thought amber came in only one color, so I did a Google search and discovered that there are different colors of amber, some rarer than others. One of the first things I did, when I received them, was try them on. They are beautiful. Like any good beads, the string is knotted between each bead. The connector is plastic, but that is so that when you secure the beads around your neck, the connection is hidden. Just be sure to screw in, not push in, the plastic connector.
I measured the necklace. It is 18 inches or 44 cm long. The product heading says it is 17 inches long but this is typo, which needs to be corrected. I wanted to see if these were really amber, and not plastic beads. I decided not to use a hot needle to see if they would melt. Instead, I used the density test. I dissolved 1/8 cup of salt in 1 cup of warm water, until it was fully dissolved. I lowered the necklace into the solution. To my delight, the necklace floated. The beads are real amber.
In conclusion, I am really happy with this item and hope to wear it often.

title: really nice!
text: I have skin picking disorder and anxiety and I love fidgets so I have wanted to try this for a long time. The product arrived quickly, in a nice box with a lot of accessories; a bottle of latex based paint to refill the stone, a large scraping tool (I assume to smooth the refill paint over the rock), and a double sided picker that is sharp on both ends. I do have a mild latex irritation but I have personally not had issues with handling this for over 3 hours, however, if you have a true latex allergy you must know this is latex paint. The included paper also says to wear eye protection, I wear glasses so I felt like that was sufficient. I also did not have any pieces fly off but it could happen! My favorite way to use the stone is to poke a "pore" of the stone and then scrape the filling out. My 7 year old is jealous of this and would love to try it but I said no because the picker tool is sharp. Overall I give this 5 stars. I had a good time with it and will continue to use it while I watch tv rather than picking at my scalp.

title: Great Lip Balm

title: Great way to let someone know you're thinking about them -- easy set-up and new VOICE FEATURE!
text: Now, I've been a fan of LuvLink from the days of the original Friendship Lamp model, and as someone who lives across the country from most of my family, the overall concept behind these lamps are great. It‚Äôs a way to stay connected and let someone know you‚Äôre thinking about them, no matter how near or far. I use these with my mom, and even though we‚Äôre on different time zones, it‚Äôs a simple way to keep in touch. I love them. The wi-fi set up was much easier in my experience as opposed to the original Friendship Lamps, so that was a definite bonus. You can even select your particular color, and I know some people use them to send non-verbal reminders based on the particular color. For my mom and me, we just tap it every now and then when we walk by, but it means just as much to us as if we were sending special top-secret messages, lol ‚Äì so, this is a win for me. The MAJOR difference in this new Infinity Voice model is that now you can actually record and send voice messages, which I absolutely adore. I am so happy to have these, and I think it's a wonderful way to maintain connections. The quality of the lamp itself could be better, that's for sure -- especially for the price you're paying. Then again, the price you're paying is for the overall experience, which is certainly worth it IMO if you've got the extra coin.

title: Innovative Tool for Anxiety Relief
text:
Five stars for sheer ingenuity and quality of this product! As someone who deals with an anxiety-related picking disorder, I had never seen a product like this before specifically geared towards a solution and that alone is noteworthy.

The product quality in this kit is great - it could potentially benefit from a bit more structured packaging to hold the items in place during transit, but that is a nitpick. The kit comes with two prepared stones, one generously covered with sequins. (I personally preferred the non-sequin option as it was easier to pull the glue off without getting messy, but that was just my preference.) I enjoyed the sensory feel of the glue and it did hold my attention and keep my hands busy. The thicker you apply the glue, the easier it is to pull off, but it also tends to come off in one piece that way. You can adjust to your level of preference when reapplying.

Now, just a note for those that specifically deal with skin picking. This is a useful tool and I fully recommend trying it if it interests you, but just be aware that it probably shouldn't be the only one you use. This is mainly because picking often happens during stressful situations that might happen outside the home, and this tool isn't something I would be comfortable taking, say, to work or on public transit. It's great for at home or another private space if you have an urge and need to keep your hands busy. It's also awesome if you just want to focus on something to quiet your thoughts or space out. However, it does make a bit of a mess, so you need to have a protected space to hold the glue bits that come off and enough room to manipulate a sharp object (if you choose to use the tool that comes with the set instead of your hands.)

On another note, this is a woman-owned small business, so it's one I feel great about supporting!

text:
This necklace is very delicate and classy! Nicely boxed, and would be a great gift. I‚Äôve enclosed a photo of it layered with another necklace of mine, and I like the look. Some notes:

-slides easily (yet securely) through a small silver ball to adjust the length
-arrived tangled but was easy to untangle
-very difficult to fasten, due to small slider ball being attached to the circle where you attach the closing clasp. It took a lot of patience and many tries to do this by myself
-chain is very delicate, shines nicely
-pearls are decent quality you would expect from such a dainty necklace

Overall this necklace is a great value, considering it is sterling silver and so pretty. This would be difficult for someone with arthritis (or minimal fingernail length) to fasten behind their neck, so that should be considered! If you have someone who can put your jewelry on for you, cheers to that, and enjoy this lovely piece!

title: Impressive moisturizing, good scent, looks bad in the tub
text:
Fizzy bath salt came in a sealed bag. It wasn‚Äôt layered like the picture on the Amazon listing and the coconut oil makes it almost look wet inside. The scent is strong when you open it but it was pleasant when it was being used it smells fruity.

There is no direction on the packaging indicating how much to use. I used a quarter of the product and it made the bath moisturizing but turned the water an unappealing yellow-grey color. I did make sure to rinse the tub very well after use.

The salt to oil ratio seems good. It reminds me of milkshake baths from popular stores, but this doesn‚Äôt have bubbles. After use I did notice my skin was softer and that stayed through to the next day. I live in the desert so that is impressive.

Product says it is made in California.

title: Beautiful Quality Pearl, But A Little Smaller Than Same Size Class From Same Company
text:
I have always wanted to have a pearl necklace. Although it is not my usual style, I thought I would try one out. The problem is that I did not have any earrings appropriate to wear with it. That is where these came in.

HOW THESE ARE PACKAGED
This is a beautiful set very appropriate for gift giving. It comes in a cardboard sheath. Inside there is a very beautiful blue box with a nice expensive looking finish on it. Inside the box there is a plastic bag with a pair of earrings, silicone backs on them, extra backs, a white velvet bag, and a cleaning cloth.

QUALITY
The earring pearls are beautiful in tone and quality. They are shiny as you can see from the photo. The camera reflection is showing on the pearl. The tone of the pearl is what I call a rose taupe tint to it. It is very slight, but it is warm and beautiful.

SIZE
The size of these is not quite as big as I hoped it would be. My necklace is from the same company and the color matches perfectly,, but the size although listed as the same is bigger on the necklace. Nevertheless, it looks good together and I am happy with it.

THE BOTTOM LINE
This set of earrings is really nice. It is good quality, well packaged, and a decent price.

MY RATING
FIVE STARS. Although I wish they were just a tiny bit larger, I still like them very much and the color is stunning.

title: Beautiful bracelet with complimentary stones

The magnetite is a nice grey color and black onyx is a solid black (no red or yellow). I like the combination of these three together as they complement each other perfectly.

The cord feels strong and you can feel the wax.

I can‚Äôt say I believe much in the healing properties but I do think these kinds of bracelets are stunning and have a fidget aspect to it. You can play with it on your wrist. Getting it on and off was easy. The bracelet came in a cushioned black box that was inside of a plastic bag.

title: Beautiful necklace.
text:
This string of beads is advertised for men, but as I think women would be interested in wearing it too. I thought that it could not be as stunning as show in the photos on the product page. In actual fact, it is just as beautiful as shown. The design, quality and workmanship are excellent. It comes in a very nice gift box, for those who want to give the beads as a present.

I can't attest to its healing powers, but I am more interested in its appearance. I measured the necklace and found it to be 21 inches long. According to my electronic scales it weighs 3.42 ounces, not 3.73 ounces as given in the description. However, my scales may not be accurate and I don't think this matters anyway.

I put the necklace on and loved the look. I can see why this is advertised as a man's necklace. It is a nice solid necklace, and not the dainty item that some women might prefer.

I highly recommend this quality item, to wear or to give as a gift.

title: Well made but cart back rest had to be modified
text: It turns out that the EZ-GO Marathon I have did not quite match the upholstery supplied.  There must have been a modification of design by EX-GO at some time because the back rests curve outwardly on the edges rather than straight across as in the pictures.  I have seen several of the same carts here in the park with the same type of backrest so It was not an aftermarket.  After removing the old covers I used a bread knife to trim down the edges to match the upholstery and found a good fit.  There was also not a plastic back cap to cover the back of the back rest so the plywood was exposed and not finished.  What I did was go to Jo Ann's fabrics and purchased some exterior black plastic upholstery to cover the plywood and screwed the assembly onto the cart mount.  Looks great!  To aid in applying the upholstery I placed the seat and cover upside down on a table and used some bar clamps to partially compress the cover down prior to stapling.  This made it very easy to install.  It has been a year or more now with two full years of Arizona Summer sunlight and shows no signs of aging yet.

title: Nice Duck Dummy
text:
My dogs are NOT retrievers but they have shown a great love for running out in the water and snatching duck decoys and bringing them back on land so I can place them in the water and we do it all over again. Pretty sure they think it's an amusing and unusual game of fetch. I figured why not try a fake duck actually meant for dogs to grab.

This duck has been a huge hit! The long rope makes it very easy to throw a long distance. It has been fairly durable except for when somebody ran off with it and decided to chew off its bill. Not the manufacturers fault. This is made as a training item, not a chew toy. The missing bill has not affected the throw or fetch quality and no one (except maybe the duck) seems to mind.

This is a good quality fake duck for the price, especially if you have pups you are actually training to retrieve a duck without biting it in half.

text:

I also tested it with a Canadian end perforated chequebook; Canadian cheques are a little longer than USA checks and the cheques stuck out about a quarter inch or so.

title: Smells lovely, cute set
text: This spa set is very giftable and smells amazing. Every element of a spa day is in this little gift set and each item comes with detailed instructions on how to use them. The clay mask might be a little difficult because it says you have to mix the powder with a TBSP of olive oil or water which would require a separate container to assemble but is also eco- friendly because it saves on packaging to be able to add water to the product instead of it being shipped with the water. The eye mask has a very cute design on it that says shhhhhh and matches with the rest of the items in the gift box. The shower cube is such a great idea because there are lots of people that don‚Äôt bathe in the tub anymore so this is a very good solution for those who only shower but I believe it said you could use it as a bath fizz as well. The scrub pouch and the soap are also a very good idea because the instructions say that it helps reduce soap waste and you can hang the pouch up after using to allow the soap to dry after use. I also love that this product is from a small business as on the Amazon listing it had the handmade title at the top of the page. Overall I think this is a great gift item, just add a little wrapping paper or tissue paper and you have a really useful and good smelling gift.

title: Fun game
text:
I like when my kids play games because it so much better than staring at a screen. This was a very fun game for my kids. They really enjoyed it. It kept their interest. title: Beautiful on my desk.
text:
Beautiful. I enjoy just looking at this. The way the ball hangs suspended ‚Äúmagically‚Äù in the top space, the colorful turquoise stones and shiny metal below is stunning. It‚Äôs well finished with excellent polished faces on the pyramid sides and base.
This is my second orgone pyramid. I got the first after I visited the summer home/museum near Rangeley, Maine of Wilhelm Reich who developed the theories of orgone energy a few years back. It was really interesting. Though his theories and ideas are a bit out-there I was interested to see what might happen if I put an orgone pyramid near my computer. The first pyramid has been there for some time, and so far nothing has happened that I can fully attribute to the ‚Äúorgone energy‚Äù, and yet my computer is still working fine, which is a positive thing. Who knows?
This pyramid is the prettiest I have seen and I love it. I‚Äôm happy to have it in my home and will enjoy it for many years.
The packaging was a doubled slide in box made in a way I haven‚Äôt seen before. This would make a lovely unusual gift. I know I would be pleased to receive it. There was a nice gift charm and thank you card with information on contacting the seller inside.
I expect good energy will definitely come from the smiles of all who see this pyramid, including me.

title: JUST THE RIGHT SIZE FOR ME
text:
These earrings are 10mm. Not too big, not too small. Fits nicely on ears. The posts are stainless steel for sensitive ears and I have not had any problem with them.

Beautifully handcrafted, they also come in a cute little gift box.

I am a bit rough on my earrings, I wear them swimming, etc. So far no problem, but the directions DO suggest not wearing them while showering or swimming.

I took one star off for the color, but that is just my PERSONAL opinion. I thought from the advertised picture they would be a bit shinier. The color is still nice, just not as vibrant as I thought it would be.

All in all, this is a nice pair of earrings for the price.

title: Very cute!
text:
These are exactly as pictured/described. They're stamped 925 Sterling silver and did not irritate my ears. As others have noted, there are 2 pairs but they are not identical - one pair is a slightly darker, more saturated green than the other pair, which is a paler version. But they are the exact same size.

Worth noting that these do stick pretty far out from your ear. They're perfect spheres set on top of the back. Most round earrings are flat on the part that rests against the ear so that they don't stick out as far. This doesn't bother me but it does look a bit different than what I'm used to and isn't as subtle or "neat," so bear that in mind. They're neither small nor big but kind of an awkward medium - too big to use in my 2nd or 3rd holes, but when I wear them in my first holes, I have to take the earrings out of my 2nd/3rd or the sizing is off. I still wear them often and love them!

text: I love long, dangly earrings.  I am very pleased with these. title: My new favorite accessory!
text: If you're looking for a way to dress up your Apple Watch for a more stylish look, stop right here! I'd never worn a wrap bracelet like this, so it took me a couple of tries to get it right, but now that I have it down, it's a breeze to put on - even one-handed! The bracelet fastens with a beautifully designed silver 'button,' through one of 3 'loops' that let you tighten or loosen as needed. Your watch will 'disconnect' from your wrist if you don't wrap correctly, causing it to ask you to unlock if you're wanting to get notifications while wearing it, but it kept up with an outdoor walk I took to test that out! It loosens a bit with a lot of movement, like dancing, but I just readjust the wrapping and it's good to go! Thinking this will be my go-to gift for friends this Christmas - really great value, and comes in a soft velvet-like pouch for safe keeping!

title: Good for skin issues
text:
My son has skin issues and has the occasional outbreak, so I got this epsom salt/sea salt product for him to soak in. Epsom salt can be good for softening rough, dry skin, and exfoliating dead skin cells. It may also soothe skin affected by skin conditions, including eczema and psoriasis. He has psoriasis, we think, and it makes him miserable when it gets bad.

He's used the product a couple of times now, and he said his rash was receding somewhat and the itching was better. He said he just felt invigorated after a good, long soak. Doesn't hurt that this product also smells nice. However, he said for those who don't care for fragrance, it might be a little overpowering for some.

While I don't believe this is a cure for skin problems, I do think it can be one of the tools for controlling the worst of the symptoms. My son is pleased, and that's a win in my book.

text: I have very sensitive ears and can wear only silver or gold earrings. These did not irritate my ears at all (and I haven‚Äôt worn earrings in a couple of months, so that‚Äôs really great). I love how easily they slide in with no need for a backer. They are very lightweight. I forgot I was wearing them. They almost look like an oval hoop until you notice that they have a unique design. I have shoulder length, curly hair and had no problem with the getting caught in it.

title: Great Picking Tool
text: These peel and pick lava rocks are an amazing resource for people who struggle with picking and skin self-harm. The silicone goo that you put on the rocks is very satisfying to pick off and easy to apply. I love that This kit has the rock already gooped up so you can start picking immediately. It comes with a scraper and tweezers and a pic as well as extra goo to put on the rock. It's one of the better kits that I've tried and the price point is great for what you get. Is an awesome gift idea for anyone who struggles with anxiety or picking.

title: Not Genuine Green Aventurine
text:
Boy, am I disappointed to write this review.

I love green aventurine, and I was so excited to get this bracelet. As soon as I opened it, I knew something was off. This morning I had someone look at it, and they confirmed that this bracelet is not genuine aventurine. It's either dyed stone or something manufactured.

If you want it for looks, this bracelet is pretty and sturdy. If you want it for the crystal properties, do not buy this product.

title: It‚Äôs labeled as both obsidian and onyx but it can‚Äôt be both‚Ä¶

The only way for me to find out is by breaking the bead to see if it breaks like volcanic glass (obsidian) or like agate (onyx), as they both *look* very similar. It‚Äôs very unfortunate. title: Very delicate & don't face forward
text:
Omg these are delicate little chains! I first tried them on with the rubber backing to see how long they were. Getting the post in my ear and then being able to put the backing on was a struggle. But not nearly as much of a struggle as trying to get the backing off! The straight post is TINY! And very thin and fragile.

Once I got the back off, I tried threading it. It stayed in place pretty well, although any slight pull on the stone slid the earring to nearly falling out. The backing on it once threaded might not be a bad idea.

Like others have said, it is almost impossible to get the stone to face forward. I took about a dozen photos of each style and the ones I'm sharing are the best I could get.

So while they are dainty and feminine and pretty, I couldn't love them. They're too fragile and don't face forward, which diminishes their beauty. I didn't want a silver teardrop, I wanted the emerald teardrop.

Not sooo sure about protection from modern day electrical/radio radiation, maybe a dense much larger section would help in that area, but I definitely believe it does help protect one from negative conscious/unconscious energy, a filter of sorts.

title: Very adjustable
text:

text:
Ages ago I had a pair of waterdrop earrings that I just loved. I wore them so much that I finally broke the wire and they had to be relegated to the box of broken gold and silver things. When I saw these I was excited to have a replacement.
I do like these a lot. They look great on and the weight is perfect. Unfortunately, the manufacturer decided to stamp 925 on the front of the drop. Someone does need to be fairly close to notice it, but it is noticeable. Why they thought this was a good idea is beyond me. I assume it has to do with simplifying manufacturing. It would have taken more effort to stamp them in a less noticeable spot. The manufacturer's pictures don't show the stamp. I also just noticed that one of the pictures notes that the earrings are silver plated. Everywhere else it just says 925 silver. As far as I know, it can't be both.

If I get ambitious I may take a micro file to them to get rid of the mark. Na, for the price it is easier to just get a pair that are made correctly.

title: Innovative Necklace, beautiful, designer is a GENIUS
text:
I was very excited to get this necklace.

I absolutely love the chain, the size and width is exactly what i like. Dainty but durable and the fact that it has this tiny bead at the clasp to move so you can adjust the sizing (as you change what you wear or your mood) is the coolest thing that i have ever seen. you are never STUCK with one length!!

When you first put this on, the stone seems a bit heavy so when you lean forward, it does hang and rotate however, you can remove the stone & beads from the chain and insert it directly into the setting so it would not do that.

Now, at first glance, that seems virtually impossible, BUT the very tip of one end of the chain is designed like the end of a shoelace!! I mean, the imagination of the person that designed this is beyond anything i can imagine....my hat is off to you!

I took the bead off that is the clasp, it has the little circle on it, the others do not (set aside and do NOT lose this one) took the stone off and the 2 beads that surround it.

In the setting right above the circles, the chain was originally in, there are triangles, I inserted the shoelace end of the chain into 1 triangle pushed in far enough and you will see the chain come out the other triangle on the opposite side of the stone setting. Pull the chain through, and insert the clasp bead back onto the chain, super simple.

If you do not mind the stone flopping around when you lean or move you do not have to do this, this was just my preference and it really only took me less than 1-2 minutes and my magnifying glass because my eyes are not great.

Whoever designed this thought of every person who may wear this piece of jewelry and what they may or may not like. The level of caring that went into this, i am unable to put into words. I hope they have additional pieces to offer, I honestly wish i could give more than 5 stars!

title: Simple, lightweight and lovely hearts!
text:
These pretty earrings are super simple, very lightweight and a bit wide and long. The metal is about the width of a large paperclip and folded into a distinct heart shape that closes on the bottom, so these are worn either upside down or on the side. The closure depends on not pulling the metal back through the tiny hole as there's no lock or security, but should be fine if you don't play with them a lot or get the end caught on something. With normal wear, they're fine and I love the fact that they can look different at different angles and distances. Nothing overwhelming, just simple, pretty jewelry for those that don't like tiny pieces. Note: If you have a very short neck or wear thick clothes around your neck, the closure might get caught on the fabric.
I do recommend care as I think they will bend easily if abused. The company really should have put a tiny smooth round dot at the end so you don't poke yourself or get caught up in anything that gets too close.
But I like them anyway.
They come in a nice gift box with a cloth for cleaning (I guess) and is ready for gift giving. See the photos -- also, the pen next to the earrings is to show approximate length.

title: Thick, Gorgeous ‚ÄúNatural Stones‚Äù but Wary of Blue Stains
text:
This 8 mm Hematite and Tiger‚Äôs Eye Bracelet is shiny, thick, and very attractive. It is woven snuggly together by black string, fastened by a Hindu metal bead with Aum, or Om, symbol on it. The store elaborated on its healing capacity, which was another neat feature. This bracelet arrived with a striking light blue velvet drawstring jewelry bag.

The bracelet is comfortable and beautifully designed. I found the clasp to be solid but also a bit sticky. The good news is I have absolutely no fear of this bracelet falling off or of losing it.

I had felt drawn to this bracelet, which was labeled ‚Äúnatural stone beads‚Äù and ‚Äúgenuine‚Äù. I, myself, have learned to double check with isopropyl alcohol or acetone, when I buy items of jewelry or natural stones to verify that the products match the description and that no color bleeds easily.

I was saddened, however, that the blue of the Blue Tiger‚Äôs Eye seems to have the capacity of staining fabric or skin rather quickly and may have been potentially compromised, at some point, even if it is indeed natural Tiger‚Äôs Eye. This may serve as a deterrent for some if the color is enhanced or by some other means may bleed.

However, consumers have different priorities in what they are looking for. This could be a fabulous, remarkably beautiful stone bracelet, if it meets your needs and seems appealing.

title: Small bottle will last a long time
text: I had been prescribed Minoxidil for the last few years, and it works, but has the side effect of very itchy scalp. Plus, minoxidil is expensive, and the liquid form can be hard to find (foam form is not useful for many women). I was surprised to see studies on Rosemary oil for hair loss show it is as effective in blind studies as Minoxidil. This was a WONDERFUL replacement for me. My scalp feels good now, not itchy at all. The bottle did not indicate how much to use, but a small amount seems to go a long way. I have been using about 4 times a week (minoxidil is supposed to be 2x every day). This seems to work for me equally well. The hair will look greasy if you apply this 2x before washing it, but I lean over and apply it underneath, or at the back of the head so the hair doesn't look as oily. The smell is very natural, and herby, not like perfume or chemicals, and not overpowering. An appropriate scent for men or women.

The black beads are matte finish, which I like visually and physically. They look and feel different from their shiny neighbors.

Seller's photos state that hematite beads are included for "triple" protection but my bracelet only has two type beads, not three.

The strings that one adjusts to tighten or loosen the bracelet have matte black beads on their ends. They are a bit long so I wear them tucked under the three other bracelets on my wrist to avoid them getting caught on anything.

They are an important part of how this bracelet tightens so they cannot be trimmed unless you wish this to remain on your wrist until it breaks.

There was not a strong smell when this arrived albeit the velvet box did indeed not sit closed properly as others have stated.

If you like the look of the beads, you will enjoy this bracelet but if you choose it based on genuine stone... you might be disappointed.

Pretty design, well made, but might not be genuine stones.

title: Fits my 7.5" wrist, stones are a bit dull
text:
Review of: "Verybegin Handmade Bracelet, Protection Bracelet, 8mm Beads of Natural Black Hematite and Yellow Tiger Eye and Black Agate Stone Bracelet." I have the double row version.
When I first opened the box, I was a bit underwhelmed. The stones just don't look very bright or shiny. I guess for the price you're not going to get beautiful shiny stones. I understood that the tiger eye might not be the best, and it isn't- only two of the tiger eyes have that nice stripe effect, the rest are mostly just brown with a little cloudiness. I think the problem is that most hematite I've seen is much more reflective than what's in this bracelet. In most light it looks just as dark as the black stones, so the bracelet just appears brown and black. As far as construction, the bracelet is well made. The slider part is tight so it holds at the place you put it. I do wonder how long it will hold up, since I have to tug on it fairly hard to get it the right size. It does fit my 7.5 inch wrist, it will go even smaller if needed, I'd guess to about 7 inches, and I wear it snug.)
I would say this is pretty good for the price. There are many of these out there for double the price or more, and I think they are about the same quality.

title: Lightweight, mid-quality
text:
Many leather journals weigh quite a bit; this one is quite light, which means it actually will be good to take along in a backpack or carryon.
The paper quality is nice. It‚Äôs not smooth enough for a nib pen, but it looks good for gel pens and possibly even watercolor. Certainly it will be fine for sketching and colored pencil.
The cover isn‚Äôt great. For one thing, the front design is busy and ugly. I hate it. The back is much better. And the design of the string was clearly not thought out well, as using the string warps and damages the edges of the leather cover. My journal arrived with deep grooves already in the edge.
The price as stated at this time is $60.00. As a Vine reviewer, I did not pay that price, but I honestly don‚Äôt think many people would. For $60.00, one would expect a higher-end product than this; a better cover and a better closure would be expected for that price. This journal is a nice, mid-quality book. I think people would consider buying it if it were priced somewhere in the $30.00-$40.00 range.
I noticed that other reviewers speak of a ‚Äúseed card‚Äù or other included literature with the journal. I received nothing of the kind, although the journal did come in a rather ugly box which was too big for the book itself. The box seems wasteful to me; a paper wrapper would‚Äôve protected the book as well and with less waste.
Overall, it‚Äôs quite a nice little book with an ugly cover.

text:
Things I liked about the YouClean soaps:

- nice coconut smell

- eco-friendly packaging: just wrapped in some packaging paper

Things to watch out for:

- natural ingredients doesn't mean hypoallergenic ingredients - some other sensitive skin products have felt a bit easier on my sensitive skin than this product
- washes off a lot of oils in the skin - might leave some sensitive skin folks feeling a bit pasty and dry
- soap washes off slippery in the tub

I think if you don't have sensitive skin, this is probably a knockout, fairly inexpensive natural soap to use. If you have sensitive skin, you might try a bar or two and see how it feels for you.

title: Perfect for my 2 and 5 year old!
text:
I ordered this for my daughters - ages 2 and 5. They both love jewelry but are still a little rough with it and can‚Äôt be trusted with the finer quality items.

What I Love
- It‚Äôs a thicker chain and the Lego-like pieces are sturdy and look exactly as advertised. Perfect for kids and adults with a sense of whimsy.
- The two pieces click together snugly but even each individual piece is attractive.
- I opened the box but didn‚Äôt have a chance to put away before a play date. My friend‚Äôs son opened the box (which is why the chains are now entwined as seen in the photo) and was running around the house with it. That said, nothing broke, the thicker chain will be easier to untangle AND turns out 3.5 year old boys love this too because of the Lego and heart shape.

What I wish was different
- it arrives in a single box, but I‚Äôm gifting to two children. I wish there was at least a fabric pouch included to be able to gift them individually without having to come up with a solution. Removing one star for this reason.

All in all, it‚Äôs exactly what I was hoping for and I look forward to giving to my kids for Christmas. I‚Äôd recommend to anyone.

title: Works exactly as described
text:
We have three dogs and a cat. Because my dogs are always trying to steal my cat‚Äôs food we feed the cat in the basement stairs. As a result, his food dish (which is a rectangular Tupperware ) is always moving and in the way.

This solved everything. The bowl is removable and dishwasher safe. The bowl holder installed easily and stays up consistently and safely. If you place in drywall (we did not), be sure to use anchors or the weight of the water/animal mouth/paw will pull it out of the wall.
