title: Well Made
text: [[VIDEOID:e10c8b7a01c8653ea2693fac82104a59]] Ok, first things first I gave this bracelet 4 stars because the Amethyst stones aren‚Äôt as dark or a rich purple as I would‚Äôve liked. In the video you can see they‚Äôre a lighter purple than the Amazon pictures. It‚Äôs more of a milky or clear purple. It was a little disappointing since I wanted a richer purple like the pictures. As for the Hematite and Obsidian their color was as expected. The Hematite looks like shiny gun metal (dark grey) and the Obsidian is a shiny black. I loved how well this bracelet is made. The stones are braided in place which keeps them secure and makes it less likely for the bracelet to break. At the end of the strings there are Hematite stones which I thought was a nice touch. The strings are kind of long but they didn‚Äôt get in the way when I wore it. I thought they may get hooked on something or annoy me by making the tapping sound as I typed on the keyboard but it didn‚Äôt. My wrist measures to 7 inches and this bracelet fit perfectly. It‚Äôs as tight as it can go and it‚Äôs further down my wrist. Meaning it‚Äôs past the bone of my wrist that sticks out going in the direction toward my elbow. For those that have larger wrists you should be fine with this bracelet. Overall, I love this bracelet and the only reason I gave it 4 stars was because of the coloring of the Amethyst stones. That‚Äôs the only thing about shopping online you can‚Äôt pick which bracelet you want if you went to a brick & mortar store. It‚Äôs ok, like I said I still love the bracelet and you can‚Äôt beat the price!

title: So much style for so little money
text: This boho Apple watch band/ bracelet is a GEM! The band is well constructed, the beads are securely fastened and the chain has enough weight to feel as thought the links won't rip off. It slides into the watch face easily as well. Something to know about any bracelet band is that it's not going to stay snug on your wrist like a traditional watch band. That is the nature of a bracelet band vs a watch band. For that reason this is unlikely to be a DAILY wear choice, but not an issue due to the bracelet band itself. I've tried several of these, and this is the best so far thanks to the chain closure. The chain allows for various wrist sizes to wear easily (my wrist is ~6.5"), but it is a bit tricky to figure out how to put it on yourself - especially snuggly. It took me about 15 seconds to get it on as pictured, but if I wanted to get it as tight as possible, I'd probably just grab my roommate for an assist. Love this and definitely going to be a go-to gift as well!

title: Beautiful Piece of Jewelry
text:
I'm always a little reluctant to buy jewelry on-line, because it's hard to tell how nice it will really look. With this necklace, I hoped I was getting a nice piece of costume jewelry. Instead, I got a lovely piece of real jewelry. This is a delicate necklace, with a really pretty chain, just smaller than the turquoise beads. I thought the description was a little odd when it said that the picture makes it look larger than it is, but now I get it. The picture had me worried that the beads would look fake or plastic, but they are tiny (in a positive way) and are just right to add a little color to the necklace. This necklace is 'infinitely' adjustable within its range, since it adjusts by pulling the end of the chain through a snug fitting instead of by having a few holes to choose from. I can make it a short choker length or let it be a little longer for lower-necked tops. I haven't included my own photos, because I feel the vendor photos are accurate.

Also, this necklace would make a beautiful gift because of the way it is packaged. The necklace comes in a soft pouch inside of a nice, sturdy gift box. A small jewelry cleaning cloth is also included, along with a gauzy gift bag - all of the items pictured by the vendor. You could send it directly to a recipient, or you could ship it to yourself, sign the small gift card included, and gift it in the drawstring gift bag.

Pros:
Fine quality workmanship
Adjustable length makes this necklace ideal for layering with other necklaces
Crimps on either side of the beads allow just a little movement but are essentially invisible
Easy to fasten clasp
Easy to adjust length
Looks much more expensive than the price

Cons:
The way the necklace length adjusts will actually allow the end of the necklace to come completely out. While you can easily slide it back in, it's possible you could catch it on something and pull it out without realizing it and maybe lose the necklace. So far, it doesn't seem to loosen on its own, so I don't think it's likely to just fall out, and I wouldn't let this stop me from purchasing another for a gift. The crimps around the beads mean they won't slide off, even if the end does come out.

I would buy this necklace again - I'm already enjoying wearing it. I don't usually write such a long review, but I'm really pleased with this necklace!

title: Beautiful Gem Bracelet, Nice Additional Necklace
text:
This tiger eye and hematite bracelet and tiger eye necklace set comes in a gift box with a ribbon on the lid. The blue and yellow tiger eye beads all have excellent luster to them. The hematite and tiger eye are all well polished, smooth, and shiny. The large tiger eye bead on the necklace has similar finish and luster to the smaller beads on the bracelet.

The bracelet is adjusted by pulling the two drawstrings. I would recommend measuring the circumference of your wrist if you have smaller wrists. I have a 7.5" wrist and the bracelet is close to the limits of its adjustment, so the 7" size on the product page is accurate. The drawstrings have a small hematite bead at the end and they do hang down after the bracelet is adjusted. You can tuck them under the beaded part of the bracelet.

The necklace is simple and not heavy. The string is made of a light nylon cord, similar to but not as tough as paracord. The necklace has collar that can be moved up and down to tighten the cord that goes around your neck.

Both the bracelet and the necklace are well made and the synthetic threads used to make them are fused at the ends to prevent fraying. There was one tiny loose spot in the bracelet's thread at the beginning of the bead section, but the beads were not loose and it didn't affect function.

It would make a lovely gift for a person - of any age - who favors the unconventional.

title: Lovely, but varies slightly from the description...
text: This is a very pretty bracelet!  The colors are vibrant in bright light but appear quite dark in dim lighting.  The beads themselves are very clear and shiny.  The bracelet I received can be adjusted to fit wrists between ~7-10 inches in diameter (the product description says 8.3-12). It could be worn on smaller wrists as well but would be loose.  The diameter of your wrist will determine how long the "tails" are that dangle down from the sliding knot.  The looser the bracelet, the shorter the tails; the tighter the bracelet, the longer they'll be.  This is a unisex piece and is super versatile.  It looks great worn alone, although I will likely layer it with other bracelets most often. My only disappointment is that the bracelet I received (with blue tiger eyes) is missing the silver bead pictured in the center of the knot. Probably not a huge deal for most, but it caught my eye in the photos and would have been a nice touch.

To avoid this, you have to thread one through the front of your ear first (on the left side) and the second through the back (on the right ear). It‚Äôs a soft pliable metal so they‚Äôre easy to put in but gentle care is necessary. You can see I misshaped one trying to figure out why they weren‚Äôt hanging the opposite/mirrored. title: Very Comfortable
text:
This will easily be one of my favorite watchband for my Apple Watch. The colors are neutral and will go with everything and I love the feel of the cool stones on my wrist. It is infinitely adjustable so that it is neither too tight or too loose. It comes with a color pamphlet that explains how to adjust the chain if you feel it is too long. The directions on the website are also well done.

UPDate 1/14/23: I discovered after using this watchband for a few days that it is very difficult to latch with just one hand to make it tight enough for the Apple Watch to detect that it is on your wrist. Since it needs to come off at least once a day to be charged, I became frustrated every time I had to put the watch back on. (If you have someone to help each time - no problem). After a week, I changed out the band for another band that was easier to clasp. While I have changed the rating from 5-stars to 4-stars, due to this difficulty, I still love how it feels on the wrist.

title: /almost Perfect
text:
I love these earrings. They are so lightweight and comfortable to wear, you can workout, run, and jump, and you will not even feel them in your ears. Simple, small and bright, with the whole design face forward, which I like better than the front to back design of regular hoops, they are a great addition to my many earrings, I'm sure I will be grabbing them on a regular basis.

The packaging is nice, with them coming in a little flat box that is sealed at both ends, so you will have to dig off the seals, alas, to allow you to slip out the flat black pocket with a white snap that holds them. This is a cute bag that will stand out, should you fling it on top of all those little jewelry sacks with the strings you pull to close them, and it even comes with a polishing cloth in a small cardboard envelope. Seems to me a lot of consideration went into the packaging, and I like it.
So, now is the reason for the four stars rather than five, which I would really like to give this pair of earrings. Yes, they are elegant, comfortable, and a terrific price, so what is the problem? To me it is something that doesn't really even matter, since I never use the butterfly backs that come on most post earrings, but instead add some of those rubber backs, or nuts, or whatever you want to call them. The description does mention that these come with the butterfly backs, though, so if you like those, or if you are considering having them sent to a friend, keep the following in mind. When I took the earrings out of the little flat bag, they did not have the backs on them. The backs were at the bottom of the bag, though I could hardly feel them in there. These butterfly backs are minuscule, as in they do not fit on the earrings. Maybe Houdini or you could work them on there, but I could not. Why oh why did I get those teeny tiny butterfly backs that feel like they are something from a collection of miniatures? This needs to be addressed. Maybe I alone got these strange little metal doodads, but I want to mention it, in case those are an important aspect of the purchase to you. Hey, if the backs are not on the earrings when you first take them out, what does that tell you?

Okay, so I have my rubber nuts on these terrific new earrings, and I love them. Yes, I recommend them, but BYOB; bring your own backs.

text:
If you're worried that the stones on this are fake, they aren't. The Tiger's Eye is genuine if you can't tell by the picture I took! And the obsidian is also real, which I have tested by taking something sharp and trying to scratch any paint off (obviously there isn't any paint) and then I took one of the black beads against a window to see if it scratched it and it did without damaging the stone. If you take a real good look at it with light, you can see through it a little bit (reddish hue).

The eyes are obviously glass beads so there's not much to those other than they're wonderful quality. Either way, this is a spectacular bracelet and would make such a nice gift for someone! Or, like me, a nice little gift for yourself.

title: Pretty but not convinced they're completely sterling silver.
text:
So I'm not going to lie - when I first opened these, I was a little bit disappointed. They LOOK kind of cheap, like department store costume jewelry, at first glance. I almost sent them back but decided to put them on, and they do look a bit better on, and more importantly, they definitely feel high-quality. The pearls are very shiny with great luster.

My one concern is that I'm not sure what the metal is. The title says sterling silver, and the description says "sterling silver posts" on closer look, which generally means that the rest of the earring is not sterling silver. I'm a little bit scared to wear them for an extended period of time and risk a rash, and I always find it concerning when companies aren't 100% crystal clear about exactly what the metal is made of. If the entire thing is sterling silver and gold-plated, say so, because otherwise those of us with allergies have to assume it's not. I'm therefore passing these on to a friend who doesn't have the same sensitivities I have, and until/unless the description is updated to clarify, I wouldn't recommend these to anyone who is sensitive to metals.

title: I'm in love
text:
I'm so glad I ordered this necklace. It's the perfect mix of cool dainty style, color, and shiny gold glam. The gold chain is tiny but shiny, the beads are beautiful, the design is great. I got the one with red, turquoise and gold, and it's so adorable. It's tiny but also eye-catching. I really, really like it and know I'll wear it all the time. I layered it today with a gold tennis necklace, and it looked great. I think I can layer it with any gold necklace and it will look great.

I love that I can adjust it to be a choker or a longer necklace. The ball slider clasp is something I've never seen before on jewelry. It's an interesting concept and I like it already. You can adjust on the fly - tonight the necklace was trying to hide behind the neckline of my sweater, and so I pulled it longer just a bit and voila. Perfect layer.

The one thing I'm a bit concerned about is that there is nothing to stop the ball from sliding completely off the end, which I don't think would happen with normal use, but maybe if you were changing and it got tugged. I love it and don't want to lose it, and the end of the chain is exactly like an earring post, so I grabbed one of my small plastic earring backs and put it on there just in case. Problem solved. My hair is long so it won't show and it's clear and nearly invisible anyway. But they should put a clamp on the end like they do to keep the beads from moving around too much (which I appreciate, by the way - no chasing the beads into place, it always will look perfect).

Love, love, love this necklace. I want to order all of the colors now. Obsessed.

They also include 2 pairs of rubber backings to use if you want to wear the clover-like stud earrings without the dangle (like for at work). It will be an easy look change to bring the dangle with you and change the backings to go out after.

These are very light, comfortable and didn't irritate my earlobes at all (a risk I have with some posts). These came in a nice jewelers box and with a polishing cloth, so they are ready to be wrapped for a holiday gift, birthday, or just a "because you deserve a treat" gift. Even better is at the price, you can get yourself one and still afford the gift pair!

I'm really liking these and can't wait to wear them to a holiday party this year!

title: Delicate and pretty
text: I am not really a fan of gold plated silver, as the gold will eventually rub off if you wear the jewelry long enough. That being said, this is a really cute necklace that has adorable turquoise-colored seed beads as the focal point. I enjoyed how this necklace felt on my neck - the little seeds feel interesting if you play with them. I feel like this is a necklace that can compliment a nice, dressy outfit or dress up a casual look. This is a great find that should keep its luster as long as you don't overwear it.

title: Beautiful, giftable and a little stiff..
text: This handmade triple protection bracelet is a beautiful thing. The beads are colorful and pop against your skin, giving it an almost hypnotic quality. The string braiding it all togther feels very strong, and maybe that's why it feels so stiff to loosen/tighten. The braid is tight enough that it can be a bit difficult to put on without an extra hand and the beads themselves are braided so tightly that it doesn't quite contour to the shape of your wrist right away. But the jewelry itself is very attractive and if this is your style, (like it is mine), then the small nitpicks wont detract from a beautiful piece that feels confident, impassioned and of course, protective.

title: Absolutely Stunning Bracelets!
text:
These bracelets are made of heavy, high-quality beads. I love feeling the weight on my wrist and the cool feeling of the beads reminds me that I am wearing it and the meaning of the stones. The colors are absolutely stunning and are perfect for men or women to wear. There is a double strand bracelet and a single strand bracelet in the box. Both are woven and are beautifully crafted. You can see that the cord is carefully crisscrossed over the double-stranded bracelet of beads to keep them secure and in place.

The bracelets come ready to gift in a small box. My bracelet came in a baggie that you might want to remove the bracelet(s) from before you give them to someone else. There is a velcro strap inside the box for you to loop around a bracelet for better presentation. My bracelets came very tight and I could not fit either one on without loosening the cords. There were no instructions provided on how to do this inside the box or on the Amazon listing page so I had to look it up on my own. It's not difficult, but I would have appreciated instructions being provided for those of us who are new to these types of bracelets.

title: Beautiful, changeable wall art!
text:
I just received my order and it arrived in perfect condition. Well packaged and well labeled, it was flat in the bottom of another Amazon order box, though there's a note from the seller that gives you a link in case it doesn't arrive without crease.

I can't wait to go get 2 matching frames, stack a full year's set of prints each in them, and switch them out as the seasons change.

I love the prints used, and I picked this package specifically because I wanted the autumn prints without mushrooms (I'm not a mushroom print kinda gal). These were well made, on good paper (glossy but not too much, good thickness and can't see through them when in the frame).

I'd have no trouble adding these to a welcome home basket or to a housewarming gift to a friend. They are classy and at 12"x16", they aren't too big either.

text:

text:
This gemstone bracelet comes in a small gift box. The blue tigereye, obsidian, and hematite beads on this triple layer gemstone bracelet are all very pretty. The hematite has a glossy polish and metallic shine. The obsidian is also very polished and some have a very interesting white streak running through it. The blue tiger eye has a luster that reflects light. All of the stones are polished smooth.

The adjustment area has a small silver bead that is useful for holding on to when tightening the bracelet. The string work is not as tight as on other bracelets of this type that I have. It is a little looser around some of the beads in the band, and most noticeably at the end of the band where the string comes together to where it can be tightened. The fusing of the synthetic cord is also not quite as clean as other bracelets. It doesn't affect its function and I don't expect it to come apart, it is just noticeable for the wearer.

It is otherwise a very pretty bead bracelet that isn't too heavy and is comfortable to wear!

title: Lovely serving or decorative spoon.
text:
This arrives in a drawstring muslin storage bag inside a fold-top acetate bag.
If giving as a gift, this would be challenging to wrap as it arrives, but would fit in a small gift bag or find an appropriately sized box to wrap. This would make a great standalone, any occasion gift for a spoon collector, or be a nice part (with some additional serving pieces) of a host/hostess or housewarming gift.
I like that it comes with the storage bag to protect it from drawer accidents (stray fork jabs or knife knicks) when not being used.
It is a very attractive serving spoon with an intricate leaf motif on the handle which lends it to multiple holiday feasts. Thanksgiving pops into mind first, but then I think about Spring & all the leaves budding on the trees & that makes me think about Easter & Ostara, so this has multiple occasions that it is ready for, including 'It's Tuesday night & I feel like being fancy'!
As a wooden spoon, you'll want to wash it by hand & occasionally oil it with a neutral food oil like olive, grapeseed, or avocado. I usually oil my spoons 1-2 times a year, or anytime they start to look dry. The more it's used, the less often you'll need to oil it. All it takes is a drop & a paper towel or a soft food safe rag (read, one that has not been used for cleaning with non-food safe chemicals).
The leaf design takes a moment to get used to holding, but is fine for serving. I wouldn't want to try mixing up a batter with it or anything, though.
The wood is sturdy & attractive. A nice piece to display as well as serve with.
I recommend.

title: Comfortable, shiny, pretty
text: This is actually a very nice beaded bracelet. I don‚Äôt know much about the luck or prosperity yet, but I‚Äôm really happy with this order. The beads are very solidly put together to the point where you would think they were fused in someway but if you look very carefully it‚Äôs just intricately braided so tightly that they don‚Äôt move, they really act as one piece. I like that because sometimes beaded bracelets get that really loose, floppy, sloppy feeling and appearance. I also note the adjustment toggle is an intricate braided knot. It easily slips open or closed yet remains solidly in place while wearing. I didn‚Äôt know this was possible! amazing craftsmanship, I‚Äôm going to have to learn to do that kind of knot. The colors are actually way prettier than in the stock photo. Very earthy neutral tones. The ends of the rope knot have smaller beads at the end. One on each. This creates a beautiful rhythmic  rattle sound if you quickly whip you wrist back and forth. I love that but if you prefer not to hear the occasional click you could easily remove those beads and this bracelet would then be absolutely silent. Because the beads are so tight, they don‚Äôt click together at all, so there‚Äôs no noise other than the extension beads. Great gift idea, especially for anyone that meditates, does yoga, or uses crystals.

I absolutely love this bracelet. It's so pretty and looks fantastic with anything I wear. Now I'm not the one to believe that certain stones have some kind of healing power, although I do respect those who believe that. I just think that they are beautiful and I have always loved them.
The best thing I love about this is that it is very easy to put on. I usually have to do it by myself and with one hand. With the type of clasp that this has, it is actually very easy to get fastened with just one hand!! If you happen to get something spilled on it, just wash it off with a little bit of mild soap and water and that's it! Very easy to take care of. It doesn't feel uncomfortable or get itchy or anything like that either. It's actually very comfortable to wear and in fact, I've even forgotten to take it off at night and slept with it on because it's that comfortable.
So yeah, I definitely recommend this for anyone really. It's a very simple bracelet that you can wear with anything you want and it looks fantastic. Very pretty. I'm so happy with it!!

title: Simple and beautiful
text: This is a dainty, beautiful necklace. I love the color. I don't know how to tell if it's real amethyst or not, but the color is accurate and it isn't made of plastic. I would love the necklace with just the stone, but the little dangling star really takes it to the next level. I like that the chain goes through the stone; it seems secure and I like that it can't slide around on the chain. It's a shorter necklace and the perfect length for me. The necklace comes in a nice box that raises the jewelry as you open it, something I hadn't seen before. However, the necklace itself is under that in a plastic baggie. It was pretty tangled when I took it out. I'm sure the baggie was to protect it, but I think it might get less tangled if actually in its box.

title: Well made bracelet
text: The bracelet is well made. The pull clasp tightens and loosens easily. The tiger eye, black onyx, and magnetite beads are beautiful and do not appear to have any flaws. The beads are large and the three rows make it more on the thicker side. The only complaint I would have is that the middle row seems to get pushed up and is not flat against the outside rows.

title: Very pretty earrings
text: The earrings are just like the way they are in the photos. They are very pretty. However, I can't tell what they are made of. One part of it feels like metal and the other doesn't. I have been getting compliments on them and wearing them for a little bit. They haven't changed colors yet or anything. I will say it definitely something you can give to someone or for yourself to wear.

title: cheesy Rudolph
text: The Rudolph is oddly designed, looks like a paratrooper soldier. The other designs seem better choices for the price. It's supposed to hang on your front door, but as others stated it doesn't have a timer for the Welcome light so your AA batteries will wear out. Either a timer or solar power would make it more useful. It came in a difficult to open envelope so when I used scissors to open it I accidentally cut the rope used to hang it up and had to tie it in a knot to make it work!
